<HEADLINE> Wizards 3, Rapids 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Kerry Zavagnin scored two minutes into
the game and the Kansas City Wizards went on to beat the Colorado
Rapids 3-1 on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
   It was the quickest goal from the start of a match in Kansas
City's history.
</P>
<P>
   The Wizards added to their lead on a breakaway goal in the 75th
minute when Milkos Molnar chipped the ball over Rapids goalkeeper
David Kramer.
</P>
<P>
   Paul Bravo scored the lone goal for Colorado (10-11-3) on a
penalty kick with five minutes to play.
</P>
<P>
   Kansas City (13-5-5) completed the scoring when Gary Glasgow
scored off a Chris Klein pass in the second minute of second-half
extra time.
</P>
</TEXT>
