<HEADLINE> Monarchs 73, Sol 55  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Ticha Penicheiro scored 15 points and
Yolanda Griffith added 13 as the Sacramento Monarchs beat the Miami
Sol 73-55 Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
   Sacramento (19-10) won its fourth straight, and sixth in seven
games, to move into third place in the Western Conference.
</P>
<P>
   The Sol (10-19) lost their fifth in six games -- all on the road.
Miami, in sixth place in the East, trails fourth-place Detroit by
2&AMP;frac12; games with three remaining for the last playoff position in the
conference.
</P>
<P>
   The Monarchs led 30-20 at halftime, and made 11-of-17 shots to
pull away in the second half. Consecutive 3-pointers by reserves
Katy Steding and Stacy Clinesmith put Sacramento ahead 56-32 at the
11:21 mark.
</P>
<P>
   Tangela Smith had eight points and matched Griffith with eight
rebounds. Griffith had 12 points in the opening half.
</P>
<P>
   Sheri Sam, Jamie Cassidy and Milena Flores all had eight points
for Miami, which was outrebounded 33 to 19.
</P>
</TEXT>
