<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Earthquake Jolts Solomon Islands  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HONIARA, Solomon Islands (AP) -- A powerful earthquake was
recorded Thursday near a remote Pacific island chain that is part
of the Solomon Islands.
</P>
<P>
   There were no immediate reports of any injuries or damage and it
was not clear if the shallow, magnitude-6.8 temblor had caused a
tsunami wave.
</P>
<P>
   One person from the region, where a few thousand people live,
called the Solomon Islands Broadcasting Corporation to report the
quake, but gave no details of whether it had caused damage.
</P>
<P>
   Spiro Spilliopoulos of the Australian Geological Survey
Organization confirmed a quake with a magnitude of 6.8 hit 10
minutes after noon near the Santa Cruz Islands, about 470 miles
east-southeast of the Solomons' capital, Honiara.
</P>
<P>
   Spilliopoulos said there was a small possibility that a tsunami
could have been generated. Such waves could be devastating to
low-lying islands in the Pacific.
</P>
</TEXT>
