<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000803.0055 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-03 02:24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 'Sopranos' Member Recording Album  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   FRANKLIN, Tenn. (AP) -- Tony Soprano's mob boss ''Uncle Junior''
is about to sing.
</P>
<P>
   Dominic Chianese, who plays Corrado Erico Soprano on HBO's hit
series ''The Sopranos,'' was in a Franklin recording studio last
weekend recording his first album.
</P>
<P>
   ''He is a fluty, pleasant tenor,'' said Dino Elefante, co-owner
of The Sound Kitchen.
</P>
<P>
   Elefante said the album, which was recorded with studio
musicians, includes several standards like ''Ramona'' and ''For the
Good Times.'' Chianese wrote three songs himself.
</P>
<P>
   ''I was giving Dominic a tour of the studio and he ended up
singing 'Amazing Grace' with a gospel quartet that was recording
here,'' Elefante said. ''It was an amazing moment. Junior Soprano
was in my studio singing 'Amazing Grace.' You talk about worlds
colliding.''
</P>
<P>
   Chianese is shopping for a record label. A release date for the
album has not yet been set.
</P>
<P>
   Chianese has been acting since 1952. His film credits include
the role of Johnny Ola in ''The Godfather, Part II.'' He has also
appeared in the TV series ''Law &AMP; Order,'' ''Kojak,'' ''East Side,
West Side'' and ''Dark Shadows.''
</P>
</TEXT>
