<HEADLINE> Albany Medical College dean resigns  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) - The dean of Albany Medical College, Dr.
James Mandell, has resigned his position to become president of
Children's Hospital of Boston.
</P>
<P>
   Mandell announced his resignation on Wednesday. His job at
Children's Hospital - the primary pediatric teaching hospital for
Harvard Medical School - will begin Oct. 1.
</P>
<P>
   Mandell came to Albany Med as chief of urology in 1994. Under
his leadership, the medical center strengthened its research
support from $14 million in 1996 to $22 million.
</P>
<P>
   The residency placement program also improved greatly, said
Gregory McGarry, director of public relations for Albany Med.
</P>
<P>
   Mandell will be replaced on an interim basis by Dr. Vincent
Verdile, who has been the chair of the department of emergency
medicine.
</P>
<P>
   Verdile, a resident of Saratoga Springs, attended Union College
for his undergraduate degree and Albany Medical College for his
medical degree.
</P>
