<HEADLINE> Baby sitter and man held in rape of baby girl  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   PATERSON, N.J. (AP) - An 18-year-old man was ordered held on
$200,000 bail Wednesday in the rape of a 4-month-old girl at her
baby sitter's apartment in Passaic, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   The infant girl underwent surgery for genital injuries she
suffered during the July 24 assault and was hospitalized for nearly
a week, said Boris Moczula, first assistant prosecutor in Passaic
County. Moczula said she is thought to be the youngest victim of
sexual assault in the county's history.
</P>
<P>
   Marios Patino Cabrera was arrested July 27. At his bail hearing
Wednesday in Paterson, detectives also arrested the baby sitter and
accused her of giving authorities false information in the attack.
</P>
<P>
   Rosalba Rodriguez, 24, was charged with endangering the welfare
of a child for failing to seek medical attention for the girl's
injuries, and later lying to investigators. She had been the
infant's baby sitter since May, Moczula said.
</P>
<P>
   He said Cabrera, believed to be a cousin of the baby sitter's
husband, lives in the couple's apartment in Passaic along with
several other relatives. They, as well as the victim's family, were
illegal immigrants from Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   The attack occurred about 11:30 a.m. on July 24, Moczula said.
Later in the day, the baby sitter told the infant's mother that the
baby had bled during a bath, but that she thought the bleeding was
caused by a diaper that had been put on backward.
</P>
<P>
   The mother later discovered the genital injuries, Moczula said.
</P>
</TEXT>
