<HEADLINE> Stocks Open Lower; Nasdaq Down 120  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks opened lower Thursday as investors grew
uneasy about earnings for high-tech firms.
</P>
<P>
   In the first half hour of trading, the Dow Jones industrial
average was down 20.14 at 10,667.44.
</P>
<P>
   The technology-dominated Nasdaq composite index was down 120.34
to 3,532.22. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was off 10.87 to
1,427.23.
</P>
