<HEADLINE> Air Force Seeks Sport Facility Funds  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. (AP) -- Congress might open the
government's wallet and pull out $30.3 million to make improvements
to the athletic facilities at the Air Force Academy.
</P>
<P>
   A bill setting aside the money over two budget years is pending
in Congress, and academy officials are hopeful it will be approved
and signed by President Clinton before the November election.
</P>
<P>
   Preliminary plans call for renovating Cadet Fieldhouse to add
51,000 square feet. The sports medicine area and weight rooms would
be expanded, and a 109,000-square-foot building would be added next
to the fieldhouse.
</P>
<P>
   Air Force athletic officials also are hoping to raise up to $3
million through private sources to help finance construction.
</P>
