<HEADLINE> Five Injured at No Doubt Concert  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MESA, Ariz. (AP) -- A crowd of 4,000 people rushed the stage at a
No Doubt concert, injuring five people who were crushed against a
railing or trampled.
</P>
<P>
   Three people at the Mesa Amphitheater show were hospitalized in
the suburban Phoenix city, said Mesa Fire Deputy Battalion Chief
Mary Cameli.
</P>
<P>
   None of the injuries was serious, Cameli said. Three of the
injured were minors, she said.
</P>
<P>
   No Doubt, of Orange County, Calif., plays ska and pop-influenced
rock.
</P>
</TEXT>
