<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Capacitor plant adds 330 jobs  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NELSON, N.Y. (AP) - Dielectric Laboratories will double the
number of its employees under its second largest expansion in three
years, officials said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The company will add approximately 330 jobs and 60,000-square
feet of new space at its Madison County plant in a $10 million
expansion, said company President Brian DuPell. Dielectric will
have about 700 employees when the expansion is completed.
</P>
<P>
   The company produces capacitors, which store electrical charges
in high-frequency items such as cellular phones and satellites.
Dielectric is the world's leading manufacturer of single-layer
capacitors, producing 50 to 60 percent of the high-frequency
market.
</P>
<P>
   The capacitors are used in the base stations that connect users
of wireless phones. Company officials said last year that due to
the growth of the wireless communications market, Dielectric
produced almost 40 million capacitors in 1999, about 8 million more
than the year before.
</P>
<P>
   In 1993, Dielectric had $6 million in sales; last year, it had
about $21 million. In 1997, the company added 24,000 square feet of
manufacturing space.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
