<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-03 15:30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> No drugs found in system of bus driver who crashed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - No drugs or alcohol were found in the system of
a bus driver who blacked out and crashed into a building, hitting a
traffic enforcement agent and injuring 34 passengers, a transit
spokesman said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Driver Antonio Battista was given a routine drug test after the
Tuesday night accident and the results came back negative, said Al
O'Leary, a spokesman for NYC Transit.
</P>
<P>
   Battista, 25, told investigators he passed out at the wheel.
O'Leary said Battista had no known medical condition which would
explain the incident and no violations during his 14 months on the
job.
</P>
<P>
   The eastbound M-34 bus Battista was driving went out of control
shortly after crossing Ninth Avenue on 34th Street. The bus
careened into a parked car, hitting traffic agent Yvette Rivera.
</P>
<P>
   The bus then jumped the curb, crashed through a 15-foot tree and
a planter, smashed into the entrance of a Solomon Smith Barney
building, and finally came to rest in front of a garage.
</P>
<P>
   Rivera was listed in stable condition at Bellevue Hospital. None
of the passengers' injuries were life-threatening.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
