<HEADLINE> Nasdaq Ends Up 88; Dow Ends Up 19  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks closed higher Thursday, erasing earlier
losses as bargain hunters successfully pulled the market out of a
slump in technology stocks.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq composite index, after falling as much as 137.21 in
early trading, closed up 87.76 at 3,746.22, according to
preliminary calculations.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones industrial average also overcame early losses,
