<HEADLINE> Gunmen Storm British Courtroom  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SLOUGH, England (AP) -- A pair of masked gunmen burst into a
courtroom Thursday and escaped with two defendants being held
without bail, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Several shots were fired during the incident at the magistrates
court in Slough, west of London, but no one was struck, Thames
Valley Police said.
</P>
<P>
   A policeman suffered minor injuries when he was hit over the
head with a gun butt during a struggle with the masked men,
authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   ''It was all over in a matter of seconds,'' said eyewitness
Richard Wareham, who was in a waiting room when the men stormed in.
''I had heard the gunfire go off, there was shouting and then two
prisoners ran out followed by the others.''
</P>
<P>
   The men who escaped were identified by the Prison Service as
Richard Hurley, 19, charged with burglary, and Ricky Loveridge, 22,
charged with conspiracy to burgle.
</P>
<P>
   Police later said they had arrested a 22-year-old man in nearby
Maidenhead on suspicion of being one of the fugitives.
</P>
<P>
   A third defendant appearing in court with the pair did not flee
with the gunmen, police spokesman Richard Goodfellow said.
</P>
<P>
   The court building was closed until Friday so forensic officers
could comb the area for clues, and surrounding roads were sealed
off.
</P>
</TEXT>
