<HEADLINE> FSU Veterans Report to School  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) -- Seventy members of Florida State's
national championship football team reported to school Thursday
with the season opener just three weeks away.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's full bore ahead,'' senior quarterback Chris Weinke said.
''We're in the best shape we can be to defend our title.''
</P>
<P>
   Freshmen reported Tuesday to have a couple days to become
acquainted with the routine before the varsity met a deadline for
dinner on Thursday. Returning players will practice for the first
time Friday and everyone will be timed in a 1&AMP;frac12;-mile run that gives
