   ''With his speed and quickness, he's got a chance to help us,''
first-year linebackers coach Joe Kines said.
</P>
<P>
   Outside linebacker Tommy Polley seriously injured a knee in
Florida State's 46-29 national championship victory over Virginia
Tech and won't be ready for the opener, creating a spot for
redshirt freshman Kendyll Pope. Boulware could move behind him on
the depth chart.
</P>
<P>
   Coaches hope Polley, a first-team Atlantic Coast Conference
pick, will be ready for the league opener Sept. 9 at Georgia Tech.
</P>
<P>
   Florida State coaches also decided to move sophomore guard Todd
Williams back to split tackle behind Brett Williams.
</P>
<P>
   The Seminoles open Aug. 26 in Jacksonville against Brigham
Young.
</P>
