<HEADLINE> Islanders Sign Taylor Pyatt  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   UNIONDALE, N.Y. (AP) -- The New York Islanders have signed left
wing Taylor Pyatt, the second of four first-round draft picks from
the 1999 Entry Draft.
</P>
<P>
   Terms of the deal were not disclosed Thursday, but it is
believed Pyatt, who was chosen eighth overall, signed for the
maximum rookie salary under the cap, $1.025 million, plus bonuses.
</P>
<P>
   Pyatt, who will turn 19 in just over two weeks, spent three
seasons playing for Sudbury of the Ontario Hockey League and scored
91 goals and 104 assists during that time, including 40 goals and
49 assists last season.
</P>
<P>
   ''I look forward to training camp and earning a spot on the
team,'' Pyatt said. ''I think I'm ready for the NHL. I spent three
years in juniors and there's not much more to learn.''
</P>
<P>
   Pyatt is listed as 6-foot-3 and 220 pounds.
</P>
