<HEADLINE> Royals Suspend Beltran  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- AL Rookie of the Year Carlos Beltran was
suspended without pay Thursday by the Kansas City Royals for
refusing to report to the team's Florida training complex for
rehabilitation.
</P>
<P>
   The 23-year-old center fielder has been on the disabled list
with a bruised right knee since July 5. The Royals said their team
physician, Dr. Steve Joyce, recommended a rehabilitation at Haines
City and that the Royals directed Beltran to report.
</P>
<P>
   Kansas City said Beltran refused to go and suspended him for 30
days or until he reports to Haines City, whichever is first.
</P>
<P>
   Beltran makes $350,000 this season and each day of the
suspension his will cost him $1,923.
</P>
<P>
   There was no immediate response from Beltran's agent, Scott
Boras, or the Major League Baseball Players Association.
</P>
<P>
   Beltran is hitting .247 this year with six homers, 32 RBIs and
10 steals in 10 attempts.
</P>
<P>
   Last year, Beltran batted .293 with 22 homers, 108 RBIs, 112
runs and 27 steals in 35 attempts. He became the third Kansas City
player voted Rookie of the Year, following Lou Piniella in 1969 and
Bob Hamelin in 1994.
</P>
</TEXT>
