<HEADLINE> Rockers 74, Starzz 71  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLEVELAND (AP) -- Suzie McConnell Serio hit a 3-pointer with 21
seconds remaining Thursday night, lifting Cleveland to a 74-71
victory over the Utah Starrz and clinching a playoff berth for the
Rockers.
</P>
<P>
   McConnell Serio tried to work the ball inside, but found herself
out on the right wing with three seconds left on the shot clock and
instead launched a 22-footer.
</P>
<P>
   Cleveland (16-12) moved within two games of first-place New York
in the WNBA's Eastern Conference and reached the playoffs one year
after compiling the league's worst record -- 7-25.
</P>
<P>
   Utah (16-13) had a four-game winning streak snapped and didn't
help itself as it chased fourth-place Phoenix for the final playoff
spot in the Western Conference.
</P>
<P>
   Merlakia Jones led Cleveland with 19 points.
</P>
<P>
   Korie Hlede, who led Utah with 18 points, gave the Starrz a
67-64 lead by hitting a 3-pointer with 4:44 to play.
</P>
<P>
   Cleveland tied the score at 69 when rookie Ann Wauters rebounded
a missed shot and scored with 3:38 left.
</P>
<P>
   Utah went back in front when Adrienne Goodson, who had 17
points, broke free for a fast-break layup with 2:32 left.
</P>
<P>
   Cleveland again tied the score when Mery Andrade hit two free
throws to make it 71-71 with 1:19 left.
</P>
<P>
   After McConnell Serio hit the clinching 3-pointer, Utah had two
chances to tie the score in the final seconds. LaTonya Johnson's
shot rattled off the back of the rim with six seconds to play and
bounded back to Jennifer Azzi, whose off-balance shot fell well
short.
</P>
<P>
   Hlede hit all five of her shots in the second half and scored 13
points and help Utah come back from a 52-41 deficit with 13:09 to
play.
</P>
<P>
   The Starrz' rally also was helped by the defensive play of
7-foot-2 center Margo Dydek, who finished with three steals and six
blocked shots.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
