<HEADLINE> Cardinals' Smith Arrives at Camp  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. (AP) -- Defensive tackle Mark Smith showed up at
the Arizona Cardinals training camp Thursday night, just in time to
avoid having to wait another season before becoming a free agent.
</P>
<P>
   Smith, who signed a one-year, $1.03 million contract during the
off-season, held out last year then was injured and appeared in
only two games.
</P>
<P>
   Still believing he deserved better, Smith stayed away from
training camp this year. He will pay a $65,000 fine -- $5,000 for
each day he missed.
</P>
<P>
   If Smith didn't report by Friday, he would not be eligible to
become an unrestricted free agent after this season, instead he
would have been bound to the Cardinals for another year.
</P>
<P>
   Coach Vince Tobin said after Thursday's workout that Smith would
not play in Saturday's preseason opener against Denver, but would
practice Monday in Flagstaff and travel with the team to San Diego
on Monday for joint workouts with the Chargers.
</P>
<P>
   Tobin said Smith underwent a physical exam on Thursday, then
left for Flagstaff.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's been awhile since he played football, and what he's been
doing, I have no way of knowing,'' Tobin said. ''We'll certainly
know more when we get him on the field and get him in camp.''
</P>
<P>
   Smith had indicated earlier that he would report to camp on
time, but changed his mind.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's proven year in and year out that you need training camp
to progress as a football player,'' Tobin said. ''The question is
how quickly can he catch up. That still remains to be seen.''
</P>
<P>
   A healthy, well-conditioned Smith would be a welcome addition to
the depleted defensive line. He was once part of what was
considered one of the top young defensive lines in the NFL. But
tackle Eric Swann was released after a series of knee problems and
Pro Bowl defensive end Simeon Rice is a holdout after being
declared the Cardinals' franchise player.
</P>
<P>
   The fourth member of that line, defensive end Andre Wadsworth,
is recovering from arthroscopic knee surgery and has not practiced.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
